{{Short description|Character in Japanese mythology }}
{{More citations needed|date=October 2021|talk=Untranslated refs in the reflist}} {{Infobox noble|reign-type=[[神武天皇]]の{{ill|Imperial Prince|ja|皇子|vi|Hoàng tử|zh|皇子|ko|황자|lt=Imperial Prince|12=draft}}|birth_date=unknown|death_place=[[Yamato Province]]|father=[[Jimmu]]|mother=[[Ahiratsu-hime]]}}'''Kisumimi-no-mikoto'''<ref>『日本古代神祇事典』p341「きすみみのみこと（岐須美美命）」</ref> is a character in [[Japanese mythology]], a male deity and the son of the first Emperor [[Emperor Jimmu|Jimmu]].<ref>『日本の神仏の辞典』p400「きすみみのみこと【岐須美美命】」</ref><ref>『日本の神様読み解き事典』p118「岐須美美命」</ref> He is the younger brother of [[Tagishimimi]] and some speculate they were the same person.<ref>{{Cite web |last=日本人名大辞典+Plus |first=デジタル版 |title=岐須美美命とは |url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E5%B2%90%E9%A0%88%E7%BE%8E%E7%BE%8E%E5%91%BD-1069200 |access-date=2022-01-12 |website=コトバンク |language=ja}}</ref>
== References in the Kiki == The [[Nihon Shoki]] simple describes him and Tagishimimi as being born to [[Ahiratsu-hime]] and [[Emperor Jimmu]].<ref>{{Citation |title=Book III |url=https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Nihongi:_Chronicles_of_Japan_from_the_Earliest_Times_to_A.D._697/Book_III |work=Nihongi: Chronicles of Japan from the Earliest Times to A.D. 697, Volume 1 |access-date=2023-03-09}}</ref> without further mention
